The paper focuses on using aerial robots for search and rescue efforts, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed model uses probabilistic methods and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also incorporates geographic data and cell phone traffic data, which suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fast approximate inference and Monte Carlo tree search, which are relevant to the field of stochastic optimization (cs.SI).
